      "side": 1,
      "message": "Depending on the path, computeTightBounds can be somewhat expensive.  I don\u0027t think we need that level of precision, conservative bounds (getBounds) should also return the right answer if the path is a point.\n\nSince we\u0027re calling this for every closePath, maybe it\u0027s worth looking into even cheaper ways to test... countPoints() \u003d\u003d 1?  Cary, any suggestions here?",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 898,
        "startChar": 37,
        "endLine": 898,
        "endChar": 55
      },
      "revId": "c84492bf3b3d8c24527d122b13a4e2ae6e004dfc",
